{"author":{"id":"1260ec7e1e5fa2a41651bb0f92ca6302285a1546d07f404ff26b865b47ab5c24"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1604594396,"nonce":"QaGn9OEzIJU/0voL0NlTkoHmaDE=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3MzcwOTAwOTU=","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/263","origin":"github"},"title":"Establish some local keyring store if there is no default one available","message":"We use keyring (as well as we do in datalad).  That one by default considers the desktop's (be it a Mac, Gnome, whatever) credential store, but falls short if session is pure terminal session.  See https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/262#issuecomment-721988907 .\n\nWhat I think we should do (instead of just `get_password`)\n- check with keyring if credential store(s) available.\n- if not: ask user either we should establish one local in his/her account.  https://github.com/datalad/datalad/wiki/FAQ#how-to-configure-insecure-local-credentials-store provides howto for a simple insecure one but we could give an option to make it secure (protected by passphrase) -- I believe keyring allows for that.\n- if yes and multiple: if we have that one explicitly created, it should be used instead probably or may be we could check if password available in any (unless keyring does it automagically)?","files":null}]}